HEADWORD: Culmiferous
<hw>Cul*mif"er*ous</hw> <pr>(k?l-m?f"?r-?s)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>culmus</ets> stalk or stem + <ets>-ferous</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>culmif⟦egrave⟧re</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having jointed stems or
culms.</def>⟦br⟧
